t.  How old was he?  Where was he?  He tried opening his eyes more and the light was anguish.  His vision was blurred beyond recognizing his surroundings.  Relaxing his eyes he lay still.  He still flexed his fingers and now his hand was capable of movement.<br><br>His mouth was dry like sand and his lips cracked and crusted with blood.  His throat refused to make a sound beyond his dry breathing.  He tried to work up some saliva in his mouth to wet his parched lips, but it was slow going.<br><br>&quot;I'm amazed you're even alive,&quot; a voice said from somewhere.  He tried to respond but nothing was working.<br><br>&quot;Poor Bowynn… You just walked right into this&quot; she said softly.  He felt a damp rag touch his lips and the pain was searing, but relieving at the same time.  Again he tried to respond and the most he could manage was lifting the left side of his body a bit with his elbow and shoulder.  At the moment he tried, an explosion from his back tore through him with a weak shudder as he slumped, unconscious. <p><CENTER>Bowyn - 24th level Hero of Renegades<BR><A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bhibernia81741 target=_blank>Realm of Hibernia, Bedevere Server</a><BR><HR=25%><BR><A HREF=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4051 target=_blank>Bowynn Bel'Aurora - 58th level Enchanter</A><BR><A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg target=_blank>Tribunal Server</A></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ubowynn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bowynn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Head Whore of Playsure Palace</span><br>  Posts: 1583<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(11/15/01 12:56:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Betrayal, Part 2</span><hr size=1> &quot;I love you,&quot; she said.<br><br>&quot;I know,&quot; he returned with a smile.<br><br>&quot;Come closer to me,&quot; she said petulantly, &quot;…that's better.&quot;  He leaned in to kiss her lips and the world erupted in white-hot pain.<br><br>His breath scraped out of his throat, too dry to give it voice.  His limbs writhed in agony, fingers and toes curled tightly in an involuntary grasp.  He was certain there was a fire searing him through his right side from the back.  He tried to scream.<br><br>A hand pushed down on his forehead, a cool hand that felt good against the heat of his skin.  He moaned slightly at even this tiny respite from the pain.  <br><br>&quot;Why isn’t he dead?!&quot; a male voice spoke, close to his ear.  <br><br>&quot;The poison didn't finish him.  What can I do?&quot; a female voice spoke, somewhat familiar, somewhat nonchalant.<br><br>&quot;Karana!  This is not the sort of work I enjoy!&quot; he shouted.<br><br>&quot;Quiet,&quot; she said, &quot;he'll be done soon, then we just clean up.&quot;<br><br>Wetness touched his hand and pooled through his fingers.  He tried to lift his hand to see what it was but it was beyond his strength.  As a matter of fact, keeping his eyes open was beyond his strength… breathing… seemed beyond his strength.  He faded into the blackness once more.<br><br>&quot;I love you,&quot; a female voice said.  It was different from before… huskier… powerful.  He tried to move, to respond, to do anything.  He just hoped she spoke again.  Her voice eased the pain and soothed the burn.<br><br>&quot;Your heart's blood flows from you…&quot; she said thoughtfully.<br><br>&quot;Please…&quot; he managed to utter, nearly without sound.<br><br>&quot;Do you know me?&quot; She asked.  He shook his head in response<br><br>&quot;Well, I know you.  Your heart pounds so fiercely yet so rebelliously.  You would blind yourself to your creator while showing traits that make her beam with pride.  You are an extremely contrary man.  Maybe it is this conflict... this never-ending clash within you which drives you.  But… it is dangerous in the extreme.  You play a game which borders on destruction.  Would you so readily risk your existence?<br><br>&quot;Are you..?&quot; he asked numbly.<br><br>At this the voice laughed like bells.  He almost smiled at the pure beauty of it.  She laughed from a deep place in her where there was joy and happiness.  She laughed with pure mirth.  His heart swelled at the sound of it.  <br><br>&quot;My dear sweet man… I am not Tunare.  It's a good thing too as I find you irresistibly attractive and the old elf has reservations about touching her children in certain ways,&quot; she said seductively as she drew the end of her finger along the side of his neck.  His eyes snapped open.<br><br>She was a thing of absolute beauty.  A human lying on her side next to him.  Auburn shoulder length hair, green mischievous eyes, alabaster skin, all robed in crushed red velvet which moved along the curve of her hip in a very enticing manner.  Her eyes studied his, her lips on the verge of a smile, but holding at a curious set.  He again focused on her eyes.  They swirled with an unnatural light and drew back for what seemed like miles.  No.  No human ever possessed such eyes.<br><br>&quot;Who are you?&quot; he asked.<br> <p><CENTER>Bowyn - 24th level Hero of Renegades<BR><A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bhibernia81741 target=_blank>Realm of Hibernia, Bedevere Server</a><BR><HR=25%><BR><A HREF=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4051 target=_blank>Bowynn Bel'Aurora - 58th level Enchanter</A><BR><A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg target=_blank>Tribunal Server</A></center></p><i></