causing him to move away from her a bit.  This only seemed to spur her on as she let a small laugh and moved to her hands and the balls of her feet.  He moved back a bit more slipping on a cushion and going flat on his back when she sprung.  <br><br>She landed on top of him, pinning his wrists to the ground eliciting a soft &quot;ummf&quot; from him.  She was a sturdy woman, as evidenced by her thigh muscles pressing against him.  She bent low close to his face.  Her breath was a mix of cinnamon and cloves warm on his chin.  She moved her face close to his and began coursing over the skin of his neck bathing him in her scent.  She moved back to his lips and struck, catching his lower lip between her teeth, biting softly.  He explored the sensation for a moment before pulling back and pushing up on her slightly.<br><br>&quot;I ask again... who are you?&quot; he said in a quiet demanding voice.<br><br>&quot;Is it so important that you know my name?&quot; she replied, seeming a bit disappointed.<br><br>&quot;It is,&quot; he replied.<br><br>&quot;Well, if it's really that important to you,&quot; she said moving to the side of him and sitting up on her knees, feet behind her, hands in her lap.<br><br>&quot;You have been to the city of Freeport.  You know of the temples there,&quot; she started.<br><br>&quot;Yes, I'm familiar,&quot; he said.<br><br>&quot;You have performed many services for the church of the twins, if I recall, you are well thought of by the people in the northern district.&quot;<br><br>&quot;You could say that.&quot;<br><br>&quot;Let's just say I appreciate your hard work and I've seen your face when you stood before me, longing and unsure.  I doubt anyone else has ever seen that face of yours.  It moved my heart when you shared it with me, knowing that it was a secret shared only by the two of us.  That is rare, even amongst the gods-&quot;<br><br>&quot;Woman, what on earth are you talking about,&quot; he interrupted backing away from her, eyes locked steadily on hers, hand arched in a perfect arcane trinsimbal and ready to cast.<br><br>&quot;Don't you recognize me?&quot; she said sitting back.<br><br>&quot;No I don't-&quot;<br><br>&quot;How about now,&quot; she said, standing.  It seemed a breeze came through the room and disturbed her hair slightly.<br><br>&quot;I'm telling you-&quot; he started as he began shuffling backwards.<br><br>&quot;You know me,&quot; she said, her skin turning to a grey marbled hue and her form freezing into place.  Before him stood a statue he had most definitely seen before.  It had been an odd source of comfort for him at times when he had lived in the Temple District of Freeport as an outlaw to the rest of the city.  He sat, hands supporting him behind him, clothes in disarray, completely speechless.  He sat staring at the statue before him.  It was quiet and still, and just as he remembered it.<br><br>&quot;Erolissi…&quot; he whispered, eyes wide and locked on her face.  First one green eye opened then the other.  The mouth curved into a playful smile. <p><CENTER>Bowyn - 24th level Hero of Renegades<BR><A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bhibernia81741 target=_blank>Realm of Hibernia, Bedevere Server</a><BR><HR=25%><BR><A HREF=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4051 target=_blank>Bowynn Bel'Aurora - 58th level Enchanter</A><BR><A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg target=_blank>Tribunal Server</A></center></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ubowynn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bowynn</A> at: 11/23/01 10:54:38 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ubowynn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bowynn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Head Whore of Playsure Palace</span><br>  Posts: 1681<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(11/23/01 11:43:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Betrayal, Part 4</span><hr size=1> &quot;What am I doing here?&quot; he asked her, still tensed like a rabbit ready to run.<br><br>&quot;You are dying,&quot; she replied sadly, her skin and color returning to normal as her features drooped sadly.  She touched his cheek, a look a sorrow on her face as he flinched away.<br><br>&quot;As I suspected.  What does this have to do with you?&quot;<br><br>&quot;I am involved in all matters where the heart is involved,&quot; she replied moving to his side to lay next to him, placing her hand on his arm.<br><br>&quot;And what does this have to do with that?&quot; he asked eyeing her hand suspiciously.<br><br>&quot;What's the last thing you remember?&quot; <br><br>&quot;My new house in Rivervale,&quot; he said, eyes closed in an effort to remember, &quot;I was somewhat of an outsider among my own people, you understand.  Nothing obvious, just a lack of connection with them and their way of life.  I always felt welcome among the halflings.  I was settling back for the evening, pondering my decision…&quot;<br><br>&quot;What decision?&quot; she said entwining her fingers in his.<br><br>&quot;I used to be a bold traveler,&quot; he said, removing his hand from hers.  &quot;I've been from one end of this world to the other, seen things too beautiful to describe and things so horrible I wish I could eradicate it from my memory.  My life's blood was exploration and discovery.  I decided to give that all up.  I'm not as young as I used to be and I have much to research.&quot;<br><br>&quot;Adventure is in your blood… it's not so easy to change to a life of comfort and ease,&quot; she said, again taking his hand in hers.<br><br>&quot;It was a welcome respite, none the less.&quot;<br><br>&quot;What else do you recall?&quot;<br><br>&quot;Nothing much, really.  I had a warm glass of spiced wine and had begun to read my book.  Everything after that is a blur, and a painful one at that,&quot; he said squeezing her hand slightly.<br><br>&quot;You were betrayed and stabbed… by someone you care for,&quot; she said with disgust.  He sat back and pondered the other bits of reality which floated around recently.  Pain.  The voices.  Was that reality?<br><br>&quot;Yes.&quot;<br><br>&quot;Yes, what?&quot; he asked, startled by her terse response to his thoughts.<br><br>&quot;That is the reality you are dying in.&quot;<br><br>&quot;Is there nothing I can do?&quot;<br><br>&quot;Of course there is,&quot; she said eyeing him seriously with those swirling green eyes.<br><br>&quot;Care to share?&quot; he asked nervously.<br><br>&quot;You could stay here with me.  Whatever the head elf says, I think I have more claim to you than she does.&quot; She said, toying with his shirt.<br><br>&quot;And what's my alternative?&quot; he said pushing her hand away without much real force.<br><br>&quot;They call me the goddess of love.  I am more than that.  You people think that it is so simple.  I am a goddess of jealousy, broken hearts, madness, and last... but hardly least, I am a goddess of Revenge.  You see, this is love.  The good parts, the bad parts, and I get to embrace all of it's aspects.  I am the girl that becomes speechless in front of the handsome courtier.  I am the man that cuts down his unfaithful wife.  I am the water that echoes in the ears of lovers at play as I am the fire that rages in the hearts of the betrayed as I am the cold loneliness of the heart that knows no companion.&quot;<br><br>&quot;Do you enjoy it?&quot;<br><br>&quot;No.  The madness and misery, longing and rejection, hurt and revenge, is pain to me…&quot; she said, looking down, a pause in her voice, &quot;but even so, there is also Justice.&quot;  At this, she looked him in the eyes, the green swirling brighter and faster.  &quot;As the twin sister of Mithaniel, I am no stranger to it's concept.  I offer you, as an option, Justice.&quot;<br><br>&quot;How so?&quot; he asked leaning closer in interest.<br><br>&quot;I can offer you justified revenge on those who did this to you,&quot; she said inches away from his face.  She seemed to be waiting for something, a tension filled the air.<br><br>&quot;And what is the price?&quot; he asked, a cynical smile curling his lips.  She smiled in return, reaching out and grabbing a fist full of his tunic and pulling him close.<br><br>&quot;The price is that you will be mine, and no other's.  The day of your death you will come back to me.  Until then you shall know no other love except battle and adventure.  I make this offer to you.  The choice is yours.&quot;<br><br>&quot;I guess my retirement is over,&quot; he said wistfully.<br><br>&quot;It wouldn’t have lasted a month,&quot; she said smiling, releasing her grip on his tunic.  She laid back seductively among the pillows.<br><br>&quot;Say what you will, I was looking forward to it,&quot; he sighed.<br><br>&quot;Then you have made your decision?&quot;<br><br>&quot;I have,&quot; he said, hand resting on the ankle next to his leg.<br><br>&quot;Then we seal it,&quot; she said solemnly.<br><br>&quot;And how is that done?&quot;<br><br>&quot;How do you think?&quot; she said pulling open the front of her dress.<br> <p><CENTER>Bowyn - 24th level Hero of Renegades<BR><A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bhibernia81741 target=_blank>Realm of Hibernia, Bedevere Server</a><BR><HR=25%><BR><A HREF=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4051 target=_blank>Bowynn Bel'Aurora - 58th level Enchanter</A><BR><A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg target=_blank>Tribunal Server</A></center>