quot;Yes,&quot; Bowynn said suspiciously, looking at Camthan.<br><br>&quot;Don’t ask me.  I'm her priest but in this I have no knowledge.  She brought you here whole and that's all I know,&quot; he said lifting his hands in front of him.  He had a small stylized rose imprinted on the palm of his left hand.  Bowynn looked at his own palms.  There was a similar rose, but on his right hand.<br><br>&quot;What is this about?&quot; he asked sharply at Camthan.<br><br>&quot;It means you belong to her,&quot; he said lifting his own hand, &quot;mine is the left because I serve her as I choose to.  Yours is the right because you are somehow tied to her beyond your ability to deny...  What have you done?&quot; he asked, part in awe, part in horror.<br><br>&quot;I made a pact,&quot; he said almost inaudibly, face gone slack, memory returning in small parts.  He clenched his right hand.<br><br>&quot;There are worse Deities to be bound to, Bowynn,&quot; he said, smirking.  Bowynn didn’t look up or smile. <br><br>After several minutes of sitting silently, lost in thought, he swung his feet around and stood.  Wobbly at first, he steadied himself and got his balance.  He put his hands on Camthan's shoulders.<br><br>&quot;Thank you,&quot; he said and then began looking around the room.<br><br>&quot;I'm afraid when you `arrived' you had nothing with you.&quot;<br><br>&quot;What do you mean?&quot;<br><br>&quot;Nothing, no staff, no artifacts, nothing except the robe you wear.&quot;<br><br>&quot;I need those things!&quot; Bowynn yelled on the verge of panic.  He stopped realizing who he was yelling at and his face calmed.  &quot;I'm sorry... I have no right to raise my voice at you.&quot;<br><br>&quot;It's okay,&quot; Camthan nodded.<br><br>&quot;I'm not fit for travel like this… do you by any chance have some traveling clothes and perhaps a pair of boots?&quot;<br><br>&quot;Sure.  Get some rest and I'll have them brought in,&quot; Camthan said pointing to a cot at the side of the room.  Feeling admittedly weary, Bowynn lay down and quickly fell to sleep.<br><br>*   *   *   *   *<br><br>Rising in the depth of night and navigating by his enhanced night vision, he got dressed in the garments Camthan had brought him.  He wandered past several duty paladins on his way to an area he recognized, eventually finding the fountain.  He walked up to the statue of Erolissi and knelt.<br><br>&quot;Goddess… I will remember my pact to you as you will remember yours to me.  Guide me,&quot; he whispered emphatically, imploringly.  He touched his rose imprinted hand to her ankle.<br><br>&quot;Bowynn?&quot; a voice whispered.<br><br>&quot;Goddess?&quot; he asked looking up at the statue.<br><br>&quot;Hardly!&quot; the words came from behind him following by laughter.  He turned his head and was momentarily stunned.<br><br>&quot;Alajan…&quot; he said breathlessly as he walked to her.  He stood in front of her for a moment before putting his arms around her in a hug.  &quot;It's good to see you.&quot;<br><br>&quot;What are you dong here?  Where have you been!?&quot; she said, hugging him back.  <br><br>&quot;That is a long story,&quot; he said pushing her to arms length to give her a reassuring smile.<br><br>&quot;Good, come with me and tell me on the way,&quot; she said looking him up and down.  &quot;You need supplies… where is your stuff?&quot;<br><br>&quot;I have no idea... listen, I may not have long, and I need your help.  I need to find my possessions, it's the only way I can do what needs to be done,&quot; he said looking at her seriously.<br><br>&quot;And what exactly has to be done?&quot; she asked suspiciously.<br><br>&quot;I wish I knew… I have a feeling that I will be shown the path as I come to it.&quot;<br><br>&quot;If I didn’t smell an adventure, I'd haul you off to a nut house, you know that?&quot; she admonished him.<br><br>&quot;I know it sounds strange, but I need you to trust me-&quot;<br><br>&quot;Heard that before,&quot; she said winking.<br><br>&quot;Can I count on you?&quot; he asked, smiling.<br><br>&quot;Well, I need to get out of town anyway, if you know what I mean…&quot; she said with a wink placing a few platinum pieces in his hand.<br><br>&quot;Gotcha.  Let me get a few things and we'll get out of here.&quot;<br><br>&quot;Meet me in the tunnel near the sewers, it's safer,&quot; she said with a smile and then darted into the shadows.  He smiled after her and looked at the money in his hand.  He walked off towards the merchant district hoping someone would still be there selling supplies.  He had a sense that there was going to be quit a bit of travel involved.<br> <p><CENTER><A HREF=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4051 target=_blank>Bowynn Bel'Aurora - 58th level Enchanter</A><BR><A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg target=_blank>Tribunal Server</A><BR><IMG SRC=http://www.visveres.com/sigs/sig02.jpg><BR><IMG SRC=http://www.visveres.com/sigs/sig03.jpg><BR><IMG SRC=http://www.visveres.com/sigs/sig24.jpg><BR><IMG SRC=http://www.visveres.com/sigs/sig29.jpg></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uoctraculapinkerton.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Octracula Pinkerton</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t board camper</span><br>  Posts: 478<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/30/01 4:48:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.game-revolution.com/games/xbox/action/azurik_james.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Betrayal, Part 5</span><hr size=1> Wow. Shit man, that is some seriously good writing. I can only hop